Disaster management teams have been placed on high alert in the Harry Gwala and Mgungundlovu Districts after a weather warning was issued today by the South African Weather Service, that severe thunderstorms will hit large parts of the Districts this afternoon, bringing a possibility of heavy rains, hail and strong damaging winds. Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (Cogta) MEC, Sipho Hlomuka has warned residents to take precaution as inclement weather conditions pose a serious risk to human life in the province. “We are appealing to all residents in the areas that will be affected by the severe thunderstorms to take caution. We have also deployed our disaster management teams to the areas that are most prone so that they can quickly assist should the need arise” said Hlomuka.